macro.title: Housing Policy Council: FHFA pushed new credit model despite GSE resistance
macro.what: The HPC concluded that the FHFA, under the Biden administration, directed Fannie and Freddie to approve VantageScore 4.0 despite the GSEs’ objections.
macro.why: Relevant development for housing and markets.
macro.market: Watch second-order effects across builders, lenders, and REITs.

macro.title: Redfin Economists’ Weekly Take: Mortgage Rates Tick Up After Strong Manufacturing Report, Key Jobs Data Delayed
macro.what: This Week In A Nutshell: Rates have drifted slightly higher today after a surprisingly strong ISM (Institute for Supply Management) report suggesting more robust manufacturing activity
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

macro.title: Homebuyers Are Scoring the Biggest Discounts in 13 Years
macro.what: The typical buyer who scored a home for below the list price in 2025 got a 7.9% discount—the largest since 2012
macro.why: Price trend signals wealth effects and buyer/seller power.
macro.market: Firm prices help builder margins; softness hits comps and sentiment.
